WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.700 --> 00:00:16.660
Hello, I'm Peter Park, working as a chaplain at
Eminent Hospice.

2
00:00:24.210 --> 00:00:29.690
The first time I started hospice work was in 2012.

3
00:00:30.370 --> 00:00:34.870
I started working in the US hospice for the first
time.

4
00:00:35.390 --> 00:00:38.370
I learned about the US hospice system at that time.

5
00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:41.890
I met various patients.

6
00:00:43.810 --> 00:00:47.890
I realized that hospice work is very precious and
important.

7
00:00:48.950 --> 00:00:53.130
I think it's been about 10 years already.

8
00:01:02.210 --> 00:01:05.010
I'm not working alone in hospice.

9
00:01:05.070 --> 00:01:13.570
I work as a team. I mainly work as a doctor, nurse,
social worker, chaplain, and other nurses.

10
00:01:13.570 --> 00:01:14.790
I work as a team.

11
00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:21.210
I think chaplain can be divided into two main roles.

12
00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:27.290
One is the SCS, future counselor, and BC.

13
00:01:29.710 --> 00:01:38.170
There are two areas. As you know, there are many
patients who work in hospice.

14
00:01:39.290 --> 00:01:45.590
Usually, when there is a physical pain, the life
quality is improved a lot.

15
00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:54.170
Likewise, as if there is a physical pain, many
people live with a spiritual pain in their heart.

16
00:01:54.570 --> 00:01:57.270
I think there are a lot of people who can't think of
it as important.

17
00:01:59.230 --> 00:02:07.090
If you get control through counseling, the life
quality is improved a lot.

18
00:02:07.090 --> 00:02:12.410
I think many people who have died in hospice are
suffering more.

19
00:02:14.410 --> 00:02:18.330
Especially, the hospice chaplain service is very
precious.

20
00:02:18.910 --> 00:02:22.390
It is important to visit and discuss with those who
are involved in the service.

21
00:02:22.970 --> 00:02:27.150
Through that, you can get rid of the pain in your
heart.

22
00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:34.650
I think it is very important to share with those who
have died in hospice.

23
00:02:34.990 --> 00:02:41.370
Through counseling, you can get rid of the pain in
your heart.

24
00:02:43.010 --> 00:02:48.510
These are the services we receive before we die in
hospice.

25
00:02:49.010 --> 00:02:53.330
After the patients die, there are many families who
love them.

26
00:02:54.450 --> 00:03:02.310
For those families, through the appointment
counseling, you can get rid of the pain in your heart.

27
00:03:02.670 --> 00:03:07.530
After the patients die, you can discuss with them
what kind of services they need.

28
00:03:11.910 --> 00:03:17.150
There is a service that we have sent to the families
for a year.

29
00:03:17.150 --> 00:03:23.270
How can we get rid of the pain in the family?

30
00:03:23.630 --> 00:03:28.990
We are also sharing with the family how to deal with
the patient's personal and social problems.

31
00:03:33.310 --> 00:03:37.050
We are also sharing with the family how to deal with
the patient's personal and social problems.

32
00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:49.610
I remember the patients who had died in hospice.

33
00:03:50.810 --> 00:03:54.710
One of them tried to commit suicide while taking
care of the patient.

34
00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:57.950
It was a person who tried to stop his life because
of the pain,

35
00:04:04.490 --> 00:04:06.830
but if he had received a little more hospice
service,

36
00:04:08.930 --> 00:04:13.310
he would have thought that his life would have
changed if he had received more hospice service.

37
00:04:15.010 --> 00:04:18.210
The other person was a person who had died in
January of this year.

38
00:04:18.650 --> 00:04:19.370
He said that he loved his wife.

39
00:04:22.070 --> 00:04:24.570
He was a person who couldn't say that he loved her
so easily.

40
00:04:26.390 --> 00:04:34.170
After he left, I discussed with my son in the middle
of the conversation.

41
00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:36.290
He said that he loved his father.

42
00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:42.090
As soon as I heard the story, I felt a great burden
on this matter.

43
00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:46.210
The other person is a person who has been taking
care of the patient.

44
00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:49.010
He is a very active person.

45
00:04:49.390 --> 00:04:51.990
He doesn't have anything. He thinks everything is
perfect.

46
00:04:53.790 --> 00:04:58.830
A few weeks ago, he told me that he has something to
say to his wife.

47
00:04:58.830 --> 00:05:02.370
Suddenly, his face suddenly changed and he started
to cry.

48
00:05:03.810 --> 00:05:05.610
He said that he couldn't say anything to his wife.

49
00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:10.630
He also talked about his wounds that were deep in
his heart.

50
00:05:12.410 --> 00:05:15.270
I was surprised to see how weak he was.

51
00:05:20.670 --> 00:05:22.890
I couldn't tell anyone about the pain in his heart.

52
00:05:24.570 --> 00:05:29.530
I prayed for him. After that, I saw his face getting
brighter.

53
00:05:32.350 --> 00:05:37.650
It was a very precious experience for me to realize
that the need for hospice, counseling, and chaplain was necessary.

54
00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:59.560
Koreans generally think that hospice is the cause of
death.

55
00:06:00.500 --> 00:06:02.040
Why should I think about hospice?

56
00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:03.560
I don't need to think about hospice.

57
00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:10.060
That's how I approach it. When I look at the systems
I learned from the patients I met in the U.S. hospice,

58
00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:16.620
in the U.S. society, this system of hospice is very
cultured.

59
00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:25.760
When the end stage approaches, hospice becomes
natural.

60
00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:34.320
Through that, they receive services and find ways to
end their lives.

61
00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:53.640
In the Korean society, even in the U.S. society,
hospice is a social system where we can think of death

62
00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:54.900
as if we are being welcomed by the world.

63
00:06:54.900 --> 00:06:59.740
It is a social system. It is also a social benefit.

64
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:10.640
Many people think that hospice is difficult, and it
doesn't really matter to them.

65
00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:20.180
Also, don't be afraid of hospice.

66
00:07:20.860 --> 00:07:24.960
It is a system that helps the society to end my life

67
00:07:26.340 --> 00:07:28.820
in a positive way.

68
00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:32.040
If you need to tap into hospice,

69
00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:36.420
you can ask and receive counseling.

70
00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:39.300
If you decide, it will be great.
